  "title": "Administrative Assistant (Fire & General Accident Claims)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Liaise with policyholders, intermediaries, investigators, surveyors, adjusters, investigators, lawyers, 3rd party claimants, sister companies etc;</li>\n  <li>Assist Claims Executive to manage and process claims expeditiously, professionally and equitably within agreed service benchmarks or applicable protocols;</li>\n  <li>Periodic review of files as and when required;</li>\n  <li>Ensure recovery claims are pursued and followed up periodically;</li>\n  <li>Compile monthly/quarterly statistics and any other statistical data when required;</li>\n  <li>Any other duty or assignment as and when instructed by the superior.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum qualification of Diploma and or related discipline;</li>\n  <li>Preferably with Certificate in General Insurance (CGI) qualifications or relevant insurance equivalent;</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years of relevant experience;</li>\n  <li>Well versed in insurance principles;</li>\n  <li>Possess good interpersonal and communications skills;</li>\n  <li>Able to multi-task, is a team player; conscientious, tactful, customer-focused and willingness to learn new skills;</li>\n  <li>Good working knowledge of Microsoft Office application.</li>\n</ul>",
